## Shortcuts to Resist

General anti-patterns the model is structurally tempted by. Each one
has cost us production time.

| Shortcut                                                                 | Why it fails                                                                                                |
|--------------------------------------------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| "Skip `[POLL]` — this is obviously safe."                                | The risk classifier is the machine-enforced gate. Overriding it leaves no audit trail and breaks the `audit-risk-decisions.sh` invariant. |
| "Assume the past-incident RAG hit is canonical."                        | RAG retrieval is high-signal, not ground truth. Cross-check with live state before acting on it.            |
| "Rerun the failed command unchanged."                                   | If it failed once, it will fail again. Diagnose, do not retry blindly. See Debugging Protocol step 2.      |
| "Fix the bug and clean up while I'm here."                              | Multi-fix in one step = no bisection target when a regression lands. See "Fix one thing".                  |
| "The staticData cache says it's fine."                                  | n8n `staticData` is process-local. Restart = loss. Use SQLite for anything that must persist.              |
| "The alert looks duplicate; I'll suppress it."                          | Dedup belongs in the alert receiver, not in the session. Silence = invisible drift.                         |
| "CLAUDE.md already covers this — no need to re-read the skill."         | Context compaction drops skill bodies. Re-read at every phase boundary.                                     |

